WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.080 --> 00:00:07.360
[vehicle engine rumbles]

2
00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:10.000
[ominous music plays]

3
00:00:18.240 --> 00:00:19.360
[Caroline] So I'm in my flat.

4
00:00:20.840 --> 00:00:22.040
and Sandy's on the way.

5
00:00:23.200 --> 00:00:25.280
He knows I've gone to the police.

6
00:00:25.360 --> 00:00:27.400
I'm the one who marked the grave site.

7
00:00:32.320 --> 00:00:34.120
[Caroline breathing]

8
00:00:34.200 --> 00:00:36.720
All of a sudden.
Sandy's slamming the car door

9
00:00:37.320 --> 00:00:38.640
and storming up to the door.

10
00:00:38.720 --> 00:00:40.520
[Caroline breathing frantically]

11
00:00:41.560 --> 00:00:42.480
My God.

12
00:00:43.160 --> 00:00:44.800
I think he's got a spare key.

13
00:00:45.880 --> 00:00:47.840
I honestly thought he was gonna kill me.

14
00:00:47.920 --> 00:00:51.960
[ominous music crescendos]

15
00:00:52.040 --> 00:00:55.840
But I was finding this anger
just bubbling up inside me.

16
00:00:56.360 --> 00:00:59.000
What right did he have to threaten me?

17
00:00:59.680 --> 00:01:01.360
He was the one that did this.

18
00:01:01.880 --> 00:01:03.640
And so I hit the record button.

19
00:01:04.600 --> 00:01:07.880
If he dares lay a finger on me.
I can take that to the police.

20
00:01:07.960 --> 00:01:10.560
"Do you know what?
Fuck you. Sandy. Fuck you."

21
00:01:12.200 --> 00:01:15.080
Sandy. why did you get me involved
in all of this?

22
00:01:15.160 --> 00:01:16.360
Why?

23
00:01:16.440 --> 00:01:19.880
What good did you think
was gonna come of it? You have--

24
00:01:19.960 --> 00:01:22.480
[Sandy] I'll never forgive myself
for what I've done to you.

25
00:01:22.560 --> 00:01:25.200
-You will for what you did to Parsons?
-[Sandy] No!

26
00:01:25.280 --> 00:01:28.160
[Caroline] I was expecting Sandy
to kick off.

27
00:01:28.680 --> 00:01:29.600
But actually.

28
00:01:30.240 --> 00:01:32.720
in that moment. he was a bit broken.

29
00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:35.960
-Sandy. you told me after a month.
-[Sandy] I know.

30
00:01:36.040 --> 00:01:37.040
[Caroline] Why?

31
00:01:37.120 --> 00:01:39.080
[Sandy] I fucking loved you
and I trusted you.

32
00:01:39.160 --> 00:01:42.840
I mean it. Caroline. when I say.
fuck me. I never felt so comfortable.

33
00:01:42.920 --> 00:01:45.560
I never loved somebody
as much as when I met you.

34
00:01:46.440 --> 00:01:49.400
And I said. "But you've just heard
about this Red Bull can."

35
00:01:49.480 --> 00:01:51.400
He went. "See. at the end of the day.

36
00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:54.400
whatever happened. happened."

37
00:01:54.480 --> 00:01:56.400
"But you weren't involved."

38
00:01:57.440 --> 00:01:58.760
"I involved you."

39
00:01:59.920 --> 00:02:02.520
[Sandy] Deep down. like.
it's not your fault.

40
00:02:02.600 --> 00:02:04.000
It's my fault.

41
00:02:04.760 --> 00:02:07.960
Him apologizing to me
for everything… [inhales]

42
00:02:08.040 --> 00:02:10.840
…it released a lot of the fear.

43
00:02:13.400 --> 00:02:17.480
[Sandy] Christ. you've done more for me
than anybody's ever done in my life.

44
00:02:18.600 --> 00:02:23.120
[Caroline] One side of my brain is saying.
"This is the loving man that I fell for."

45
00:02:24.160 --> 00:02:25.560
"The gentle Sandy."

46
00:02:26.280 --> 00:02:29.480
The other side of my brain is saying.
"Caroline. this guy's dangerous."

47
00:02:30.920 --> 00:02:33.040
My emotions were all over the place.

48
00:02:35.400 --> 00:02:37.400
[exhales]

49
00:02:38.800 --> 00:02:40.760
[dramatic music plays]

50
00:02:40.840 --> 00:02:43.600
Sandy and I decided
we would stay in touch.

51
00:02:43.680 --> 00:02:45.640
and he went back to the estate.

52
00:02:48.040 --> 00:02:50.400
Now. Sandy didn't hurt me that night.

53
00:02:50.480 --> 00:02:53.280
but it could've gone
a very. very different way.

54
00:02:55.400 --> 00:02:56.560
I went to the police.

55
00:02:57.440 --> 00:02:59.200
I'd done the right thing.

56
00:02:59.720 --> 00:03:02.640
But I thought.
"The police will support me through this."

57
00:03:03.160 --> 00:03:04.560
And they didn't.

58
00:03:04.640 --> 00:03:08.400
They just completely revealed me
as the betrayer.

59
00:03:09.040 --> 00:03:11.760
It made me see the police
in an entirely different light.

60
00:03:12.280 --> 00:03:13.760
[officer] What is your complaint?

61
00:03:14.280 --> 00:03:17.680
[Caroline] Do you understand how much
me going to help you guys

62
00:03:17.760 --> 00:03:20.200
has literally ruined my life?

63
00:03:20.280 --> 00:03:22.680
And you couldn't even promise me safety.

64
00:03:22.760 --> 00:03:23.880
[weeps]

65
00:03:23.960 --> 00:03:27.520
Do you understand
why this is so sad and serious?

66
00:03:27.600 --> 00:03:30.040
[dark music plays]

67
00:03:30.640 --> 00:03:32.600
The police abandoned me that day.

68
00:03:36.120 --> 00:03:39.240
[dramatic string sting]

69
00:03:46.920 --> 00:03:49.280
[David]
As head of Homicide and Major Crime.

70
00:03:49.360 --> 00:03:52.200
I had investigated many. many murders.

71
00:03:53.240 --> 00:03:55.320
Every one of them is a jigsaw.

72
00:03:55.840 --> 00:03:58.080
You don't necessarily have all the pieces.

73
00:03:58.160 --> 00:04:00.560
but you have to put together enough

74
00:04:00.640 --> 00:04:04.440
to present
that compelling picture to a jury.

75
00:04:05.560 --> 00:04:07.280
At this stage in the investigation.

76
00:04:07.360 --> 00:04:11.840
the information that we had
from Dr. Muirhead led us to the body.

77
00:04:11.920 --> 00:04:17.120
but it wasn't sufficient to allow us
to take proceedings against the McKellars.

78
00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:21.160
We needed to find
more pieces of the jigsaw.

79
00:04:21.240 --> 00:04:22.720
[dark music plays]

80
00:04:22.800 --> 00:04:25.880
The police were conducting
very. very extensive searches

81
00:04:25.960 --> 00:04:27.640
to see if they could recover

82
00:04:27.720 --> 00:04:31.080
Tony Parsons' bicycle.
his helmet. his rucksack.

83
00:04:31.600 --> 00:04:35.120
We needed to find out
what vehicle had been involved.

84
00:04:35.200 --> 00:04:37.520
It was essential that we recover

85
00:04:37.600 --> 00:04:41.280
every single possible shred
of forensic evidence.

86
00:04:41.360 --> 00:04:47.280
so that we don't allow them to get away
without any consequence of their actions.

87
00:04:47.360 --> 00:04:49.280
[dark music continues]

88
00:04:49.360 --> 00:04:50.520
On top of that.

89
00:04:50.600 --> 00:04:55.000
Dr. Muirhead told the police
that Robert McKellar had confirmed to her

90
00:04:55.080 --> 00:04:59.680
that Tony Parsons was alive at the time
they removed him to the estate.

91
00:05:01.120 --> 00:05:02.720
If he was still alive.

92
00:05:02.800 --> 00:05:06.280
that takes you into the territory
of murder or culpable homicide.

93
00:05:09.240 --> 00:05:13.680
In order to corroborate
what has been said to her.

94
00:05:13.760 --> 00:05:16.640
we need to conduct
a full postmortem examination.

95
00:05:18.360 --> 00:05:21.640
In this case.
the receiving mortuary would be

96
00:05:21.720 --> 00:05:24.360
the Queen Elizabeth Hospital Mortuary
in Glasgow.

97
00:05:25.800 --> 00:05:26.960
[Caroline] Incredibly.

98
00:05:27.680 --> 00:05:30.760
the human remains of Tony Parsons

99
00:05:30.840 --> 00:05:33.920
was brought to the same mortuary
I was contracted to work at.

100
00:05:35.880 --> 00:05:40.080
For which I had specialist access
to files. to computer programs.

101
00:05:40.160 --> 00:05:41.760
ID badges. staff access.

102
00:05:42.640 --> 00:05:48.080
It really wasn't appropriate that
she should be in or around the mortuary

103
00:05:48.160 --> 00:05:50.400
during the time
Mr. Parsons' body was there.

104
00:05:51.080 --> 00:05:54.160
[Caroline] I was then put initially
on special leave.

105
00:05:54.240 --> 00:05:56.640
in case I became a conflict of interest.

106
00:05:57.760 --> 00:06:00.640
I didn't anticipate
there would be any problem for her.

107
00:06:02.360 --> 00:06:03.760
[Caroline] I was devastated.

108
00:06:04.440 --> 00:06:05.960
I loved my job.

109
00:06:07.520 --> 00:06:08.960
[dark music continues]

110
00:06:11.520 --> 00:06:16.040
[James] In medicine.
work does kind of become all-consuming.

111
00:06:16.760 --> 00:06:19.400
It's just all you do. all you talk about.

112
00:06:19.480 --> 00:06:21.400
[pensive music plays]

113
00:06:21.480 --> 00:06:26.120
She'd have been training
for 11 years by that stage.

114
00:06:26.200 --> 00:06:29.680
Every day has been
about medical school or work as a doctor.

115
00:06:30.200 --> 00:06:34.040
To have that taken away from you.
it's devastating. That's all you have.

116
00:06:35.280 --> 00:06:37.560
Suddenly. you're at home.

117
00:06:37.640 --> 00:06:39.360
There's no one to speak to.

118
00:06:39.960 --> 00:06:42.200
And this was during lockdown.

119
00:06:42.720 --> 00:06:43.760
[pensive music continues]

120
00:06:43.840 --> 00:06:45.200
Left to her own thoughts.

121
00:06:45.280 --> 00:06:46.520
Oh. my life!

122
00:06:47.120 --> 00:06:50.120
[James] It must have been
extremely distressing for her.

123
00:06:50.800 --> 00:06:52.000
[Caroline] It was difficult.

124
00:06:53.320 --> 00:06:55.560
I had no purpose. nothing to wake up for.

125
00:06:55.640 --> 00:06:56.640
Oh. my gosh.

126
00:06:56.720 --> 00:06:59.520
I would start recording everything.
even myself.

127
00:07:00.160 --> 00:07:02.320
trying to keep a grasp on my own reality.

128
00:07:03.440 --> 00:07:05.560
[pensive music continues]

129
00:07:07.080 --> 00:07:08.760
[Margaret] It was a terrible time.

130
00:07:09.720 --> 00:07:11.560
She became totally paranoid.

131
00:07:11.640 --> 00:07:12.680
-[Stephen] Mm-hm.
-Um…

132
00:07:12.760 --> 00:07:13.920
And anti-police.

133
00:07:14.560 --> 00:07:16.760
[Margaret] Anti seeing anyone.
talking to anyone.

134
00:07:16.840 --> 00:07:18.480
doing anything.

135
00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:23.040
[Caroline] I felt like such a failure
to my parents by this point in my life.

136
00:07:23.640 --> 00:07:26.680
I knew I'd thrown
their world into turmoil.

137
00:07:27.200 --> 00:07:29.680
[phone buzzes]

138
00:07:29.760 --> 00:07:31.560
And I couldn't face that.

139
00:07:31.640 --> 00:07:33.640
[somber music playing]

140
00:07:35.280 --> 00:07:37.760
My mum explicitly asked the detectives

141
00:07:37.840 --> 00:07:40.840
if I could have someone
professional to talk to.

142
00:07:41.520 --> 00:07:44.480
The officer said. "Your daughter's
not allowed to speak to anyone.

143
00:07:44.560 --> 00:07:46.320
or she could compromise the case."

144
00:07:48.800 --> 00:07:51.440
[somber music fades]

145
00:07:51.520 --> 00:07:53.600
My support network of colleagues was gone.

146
00:07:54.320 --> 00:07:56.520
My family was torn apart by this.

147
00:07:56.600 --> 00:07:58.920
I had nothing in Glasgow.

148
00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:00.520
[dramatic string music plays]

149
00:08:00.600 --> 00:08:03.240
[James] I was getting
occasional messages from Caroline.

150
00:08:03.320 --> 00:08:05.360
She was a mess.

151
00:08:05.440 --> 00:08:08.120
You know.
a whirlwind romance. an engagement…

152
00:08:08.200 --> 00:08:12.800
I don't know if you have an opportunity
to suddenly turn those feelings off.

153
00:08:13.840 --> 00:08:16.080
[Caroline] I was so broken
and feeling as if

154
00:08:16.160 --> 00:08:17.520
no one would want to be with me.

155
00:08:18.520 --> 00:08:21.480
Sandy would send
little photos and little videos.

156
00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:24.640
saying. "Oh. my gosh. I miss you so much."

157
00:08:25.240 --> 00:08:27.680
I had handed him in and ruined his life.

158
00:08:28.840 --> 00:08:30.560
He should hate me.

159
00:08:31.680 --> 00:08:34.880
It made me feel loved.
made me feel wanted.

160
00:08:35.840 --> 00:08:39.280
And that… feeling of being treated well

161
00:08:39.360 --> 00:08:41.240
when you've not been.

162
00:08:41.320 --> 00:08:43.800
you cling onto it so strongly.

163
00:08:44.960 --> 00:08:48.400
I still had that toxic draw

164
00:08:48.480 --> 00:08:50.280
when he would message me.

165
00:08:50.360 --> 00:08:52.640
[Sandy] You make me smile
more than anybody.

166
00:08:52.720 --> 00:08:53.920
[Caroline laughs]

167
00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:56.960
[Sandy] You make me laugh
more than anybody's done in my life.

168
00:08:57.560 --> 00:09:01.200
I've never met somebody like you
before in my life.

169
00:09:01.280 --> 00:09:03.720
[dramatic string music continues]

170
00:09:03.800 --> 00:09:05.960
[Caroline]
As mad as it may sound to people.

171
00:09:06.920 --> 00:09:10.800
you can't just turn your affection off
even if they've done a terrible thing.

172
00:09:14.880 --> 00:09:16.400
I drove to the Auch Estate.

173
00:09:17.160 --> 00:09:18.480
back to Sandy.

174
00:09:19.920 --> 00:09:22.000
It weirdly felt like I was going home.

175
00:09:23.120 --> 00:09:24.920
Being somewhere where maybe…

176
00:09:25.000 --> 00:09:26.800
[dramatic string music continues]

177
00:09:26.880 --> 00:09:27.960
…I'm actually loved.

178
00:09:30.320 --> 00:09:33.200
Even if it's the most
warped love in the world.

179
00:09:36.440 --> 00:09:37.920
We've all. at some point.

180
00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:40.880
done or kept to something
we know is bad for us.

181
00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:45.160
We're all human.

182
00:09:54.120 --> 00:09:56.200
[dramatic string music fades out]

183
00:09:56.280 --> 00:09:57.160
[Caroline] Morning!

184
00:10:00.120 --> 00:10:01.320
[chuckles]

185
00:10:02.880 --> 00:10:04.960
Aye… [grunts]

186
00:10:05.040 --> 00:10:09.080
Being on that estate. you could
hide yourself away from the world.

187
00:10:11.280 --> 00:10:13.200
Ah. to be alone in Scotland.

188
00:10:13.680 --> 00:10:14.920
Yeah.

189
00:10:15.000 --> 00:10:21.040
Sandy and I. thereafter. lived in a bubble
of our own little false reality.

190
00:10:23.160 --> 00:10:24.360
[distorted] It's just the best.

191
00:10:24.440 --> 00:10:27.720
[regular voice] His brother. Robert.
he accepted me back.

192
00:10:28.240 --> 00:10:30.000
I remember Robert once saying.

193
00:10:30.080 --> 00:10:32.760
"This is the most fucked-up.
dysfunctional situation.

194
00:10:32.840 --> 00:10:34.160
but we all love each other."

195
00:10:34.240 --> 00:10:36.240
[sad string music plays]

196
00:10:38.200 --> 00:10:41.520
Me. Robert. and Sandy were
the only three in the world who knew

197
00:10:41.600 --> 00:10:43.960
the intensity of what was going on.

198
00:10:44.760 --> 00:10:47.520
When you're on the estate
and the police turn up…

199
00:10:47.600 --> 00:10:50.840
Every time a police car would even come
past the road. everyone would freeze.

200
00:10:52.320 --> 00:10:54.840
thinking they were gonna get rearrested.

201
00:10:55.640 --> 00:10:59.840
[David] I was made aware by the police
that she was back living with him.

202
00:10:59.920 --> 00:11:05.000
And it seemed to me
to be a very. very odd decision. indeed.

203
00:11:05.080 --> 00:11:07.000
[sad string music continues]

204
00:11:07.080 --> 00:11:08.920
He had told her he'd killed somebody.

205
00:11:12.600 --> 00:11:14.960
[reporter] A funeral has taken place
of a charity cyclist

206
00:11:15.040 --> 00:11:18.480
whose body was found
three years after he went missing.

207
00:11:23.080 --> 00:11:26.440
[David] The fact that
she was still associating with Sandy

208
00:11:26.960 --> 00:11:30.720
certainly created in my mind
a-- a nagging worry or concern

209
00:11:30.800 --> 00:11:37.400
that she may not be willing to participate
as a witness at a later stage.

210
00:11:40.880 --> 00:11:42.720
[sad string music continues]

211
00:11:42.800 --> 00:11:47.040
She told me that she was moving
back to the boys' estate.

212
00:11:47.840 --> 00:11:49.680
That sounded completely mental.

213
00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:54.080
I didn't know what she was doing.

214
00:11:57.400 --> 00:12:02.680
[man] How do you think people will judge
that decision to go back to the farm?

215
00:12:05.040 --> 00:12:07.120
[sad string music fades out]

216
00:12:07.200 --> 00:12:09.560
My brain couldn't fathom
and cope with the idea

217
00:12:09.640 --> 00:12:13.600
that the man that I'd fallen in love with
was a murderer.

218
00:12:14.520 --> 00:12:15.760
And I was able to…

219
00:12:15.840 --> 00:12:18.640
Poor coping strategies or whatever.
I was able to change my beliefs.

220
00:12:18.720 --> 00:12:20.560
I'd be like. "It's the parents' fault."

221
00:12:20.640 --> 00:12:24.280
"He had a bad childhood."
"Didn't mean it." "Under the influence…"

222
00:12:24.360 --> 00:12:27.960
Or. "If I do this. I can improve.
I can change this. I can control this."

223
00:12:28.040 --> 00:12:29.320
[inhales deeply]

224
00:12:30.840 --> 00:12:34.120
That little bit of your brain
that holds onto this idea

225
00:12:34.200 --> 00:12:37.920
that. "Maybe I was wrong.
maybe they are a good person." which is…

226
00:12:41.280 --> 00:12:44.360
And… we had a bond.

227
00:12:44.440 --> 00:12:47.080
which. obviously. is not healthy at all.

228
00:12:47.160 --> 00:12:50.000
but it was a bond.
and there was an awful lot of love.

229
00:12:50.080 --> 00:12:52.800
[sad string music plays]

230
00:12:52.880 --> 00:12:55.240
Love is such a strong emotion.

231
00:12:55.320 --> 00:12:59.040
It pulls you away from the reality
because reality is too painful.

232
00:12:59.960 --> 00:13:04.640
In this moment.
I was desperate to see the good in Sandy.

233
00:13:04.720 --> 00:13:06.480
[sad string music continues]

234
00:13:08.440 --> 00:13:11.720
[James] Deep down.
she didn't want the reality to be that…

235
00:13:11.800 --> 00:13:12.840
[Caroline] Hello. friend.

236
00:13:12.920 --> 00:13:16.760
…this person that she'd fallen for
had killed somebody.

237
00:13:16.840 --> 00:13:18.840
[Caroline pants]

238
00:13:18.920 --> 00:13:21.920
[Margaret] I think Caroline wanted. hoped.

239
00:13:22.440 --> 00:13:24.520
that Sandy had admitted it to her

240
00:13:24.600 --> 00:13:27.240
so that. actually.
he could redeem himself.

241
00:13:27.320 --> 00:13:28.360
[exhales]

242
00:13:28.440 --> 00:13:30.560
-You found it very hard to…
-I did. yeah.

243
00:13:30.640 --> 00:13:36.520
I think she should just have cut the ties
and… and distanced herself.

244
00:13:43.160 --> 00:13:47.120
So. at this point. we're still awaiting
the pathologist's written opinion.

245
00:13:47.200 --> 00:13:49.200
[grim music plays]

246
00:13:51.440 --> 00:13:55.400
The police did what they could
to search for Mr. Parsons' possessions.

247
00:13:56.040 --> 00:13:59.600
But no trace of his bicycle
or his equipment had been found.

248
00:14:01.720 --> 00:14:05.480
What they did discover was
