I was gonna get torn to shreds.

497
00:27:50.040 --> 00:27:53.240
[Brian] The most common question
one gets is.

498
00:27:53.320 --> 00:27:57.840
"How can you defend
people who are accused of murder?"

499
00:27:57.920 --> 00:27:59.160
My answer to that is.

500
00:27:59.240 --> 00:28:02.880
"It's not my job to decide
whether the person is innocent or guilty."

501
00:28:02.960 --> 00:28:06.720
"My task is simply to represent someone
to the best of my ability."

502
00:28:06.800 --> 00:28:07.880
[rhythmic music plays]

503
00:28:07.960 --> 00:28:10.480
When I first met Mr. McKellar.

504
00:28:10.560 --> 00:28:14.200
he no longer disputed
that he and his brother

505
00:28:14.280 --> 00:28:16.680
killed and buried Mr. Parsons.

506
00:28:16.760 --> 00:28:18.560
On his instructions.

507
00:28:18.640 --> 00:28:21.640
I approached the Crown
offering a plea of guilty

508
00:28:21.720 --> 00:28:23.960
to causing death by dangerous driving.

509
00:28:24.040 --> 00:28:25.160
[rhythmic music continues]

510
00:28:25.240 --> 00:28:29.240
But I was informed
that such a plea would not be accepted.

511
00:28:29.760 --> 00:28:32.840
The Crown intended to proceed
with a charge of murder.

512
00:28:34.080 --> 00:28:37.480
The Crown's principal sources of evidence

513
00:28:37.560 --> 00:28:41.240
were the statement from Caroline Muirhead

514
00:28:41.320 --> 00:28:43.440
that there had been a confession

515
00:28:43.520 --> 00:28:46.760
that Mr. Parsons had been alive
at the time of the collision.

516
00:28:46.840 --> 00:28:51.200
a matter which I think it's only fair
to say Mr. McKellar totally disputed.

517
00:28:52.040 --> 00:28:54.840
The other evidence was a report

518
00:28:55.440 --> 00:29:00.200
saying that it was theoretically possible
Mr. Parsons had survived the impact.

519
00:29:00.280 --> 00:29:04.880
But the Crown's expert
was really expressing an opinion.

520
00:29:04.960 --> 00:29:10.280
It was not sufficient. in my view.
to take the Crown to a charge of murder.

521
00:29:11.560 --> 00:29:15.920
Their entire case. in my opinion.
was built around one witness.

522
00:29:16.000 --> 00:29:17.600
[groans]

523
00:29:17.680 --> 00:29:20.360
And in my opinion.

524
00:29:20.440 --> 00:29:24.840
Miss Muirhead was unreliable as a witness.

525
00:29:24.920 --> 00:29:27.720
[rhythmic music continues]

526
00:29:27.800 --> 00:29:30.720
[Caroline] Following the arrest.
I'm still in this limbo.

527
00:29:30.800 --> 00:29:33.240
Until it's resolved in the courts.

528
00:29:33.320 --> 00:29:38.600
you still haven't shaken off
that shadow of what's happened.

529
00:29:39.280 --> 00:29:41.280
It's a very long waiting room.

530
00:29:41.360 --> 00:29:43.360
[grim music plays]

531
00:29:49.600 --> 00:29:53.320
All great stories do not start with.
"I bought a box of home hair dye."

532
00:29:53.400 --> 00:29:55.280
but I went. "Do you know what? Fuck it."

533
00:29:56.840 --> 00:29:57.680
Wow.

534
00:29:58.840 --> 00:29:59.680
Wow.

535
00:30:01.120 --> 00:30:04.640
I didn't want to even think
about my old life or my old reality.

536
00:30:04.720 --> 00:30:06.120
It is bad. isn't it?

537
00:30:06.760 --> 00:30:09.440
The trial date was set for July.

538
00:30:09.520 --> 00:30:11.800
I was told I would be cross-examined

539
00:30:11.880 --> 00:30:13.480
by both Robert's barrister

540
00:30:14.080 --> 00:30:16.240
and then Sandy's. back-to-back.

541
00:30:16.960 --> 00:30:20.400
I'm worried that they will destroy
my character to such an extent

542
00:30:21.040 --> 00:30:24.160
that I might never be able
to practice medicine again.

543
00:30:24.680 --> 00:30:25.760
And. you know.

544
00:30:26.560 --> 00:30:28.240
the human brain can do

545
00:30:29.120 --> 00:30:31.560
some really wild things
when it's under pressure.

546
00:30:32.600 --> 00:30:34.160
Doing a 1:00 a.m. hike.

547
00:30:34.240 --> 00:30:36.880
I started hanging with a crowd in Glasgow
I shouldn't have been with.

548
00:30:36.960 --> 00:30:38.760
[woman] ♪ Talk to me. baby ♪

549
00:30:39.320 --> 00:30:41.440
[Caroline] And I turned
to drugs and alcohol.

550
00:30:42.960 --> 00:30:44.280
Namely. cocaine.

551
00:30:45.720 --> 00:30:47.160
I was on a path of destruction.

552
00:30:48.360 --> 00:30:50.280
Caroline. when I first met her.

553
00:30:50.360 --> 00:30:53.400
was the last person on earth
who would have ever taken drugs.

554
00:30:54.000 --> 00:30:56.640
But after she met Sandy.

555
00:30:56.720 --> 00:30:59.080
she'd been taking drugs pretty regularly.

556
00:30:59.160 --> 00:31:03.160
That had coincided with her life
completely spiraling out of control.

557
00:31:03.240 --> 00:31:06.600
This is why I don't do ketamine.

558
00:31:07.080 --> 00:31:10.400
There's been times she didn't come home.

559
00:31:10.480 --> 00:31:13.480
times when we… we thought we'd lost her.

560
00:31:16.280 --> 00:31:18.160
[Brian]
According to a number of witnesses.

561
00:31:18.760 --> 00:31:21.360
Miss Muirhead was
significantly under the influence

562
00:31:21.440 --> 00:31:23.400
of both drugs and alcohol.

563
00:31:23.920 --> 00:31:28.480
That would. in my opinion.
impact upon a jury's view

564
00:31:28.560 --> 00:31:32.920
as to whether what she was telling
the police was. in fact. accurate or not.

565
00:31:34.320 --> 00:31:39.960
That. together with Miss Muirhead's
decision to continue the relationship.

566
00:31:40.040 --> 00:31:41.680
would be the starting point

567
00:31:41.760 --> 00:31:45.760
of discrediting Miss Muirhead
as a witness.

568
00:31:46.800 --> 00:31:51.760
If the jury could not be satisfied
about her evidence.

569
00:31:51.840 --> 00:31:55.280
then that would mean
they could not convict of murder.

570
00:31:56.720 --> 00:31:59.200
[Caroline] At this point.
I am saying repeatedly.

571
00:31:59.280 --> 00:32:01.760
especially to the Victim Support Services.

572
00:32:01.840 --> 00:32:04.040
I am not in a fit place to do this.

573
00:32:05.320 --> 00:32:07.000
[David] I was concerned about her.

574
00:32:07.080 --> 00:32:08.840
I was concerned for her.

575
00:32:08.920 --> 00:32:11.200
But she had placed herself in a situation

576
00:32:11.280 --> 00:32:14.840
where the Crown had no option
other than to compel her to come to court.

577
00:32:15.880 --> 00:32:19.200
And I wrote a letter to her
explaining that.

578
00:32:20.040 --> 00:32:23.160
[Caroline] This letter. it said.
if I didn't testify.

579
00:32:23.240 --> 00:32:25.600
I'd be held in contempt of court.

580
00:32:25.680 --> 00:32:29.600
It was. "You do this.
or you'll end up in jail yourself."

581
00:32:29.680 --> 00:32:32.040
I was just trying to help her.

582
00:32:32.560 --> 00:32:35.240
Because I'm looking
at this situation. thinking.

583
00:32:35.320 --> 00:32:37.280
"You're about to throw your life away."

584
00:32:37.360 --> 00:32:39.400
"You're a young. intelligent woman

585
00:32:39.480 --> 00:32:41.640
with a fantastic career in front of you.

586
00:32:41.720 --> 00:32:45.120
and you're about to literally pull the pin
on the grenade and go. 'Boom.'"

587
00:32:45.200 --> 00:32:47.200
[grim music continues]

588
00:32:48.480 --> 00:32:50.720
[Frances] There are ways to convey

589
00:32:50.800 --> 00:32:57.680
the consequences of not turning up
without it being blunt.

590
00:32:59.080 --> 00:33:00.560
As a Crown witness.

591
00:33:00.640 --> 00:33:05.000
Dr. Muirhead should have been
offered the special measure

592
00:33:05.080 --> 00:33:08.680
of having her evidence
taken by a commissioner.

593
00:33:09.560 --> 00:33:12.440
It's a procedure for vulnerable witnesses

594
00:33:12.520 --> 00:33:16.880
where the evidence is recorded
long before the trial process.

595
00:33:17.480 --> 00:33:20.440
[David] In my view.
she didn't fit the criteria.

596
00:33:20.520 --> 00:33:23.000
I'm a prosecutor.
My job is to prosecute people.

597
00:33:23.600 --> 00:33:28.120
Her giving evidence in person
would be much more impactful to a jury.

598
00:33:29.240 --> 00:33:31.960
I wasn't the strong person
who'd gone to give them evidence.

599
00:33:32.040 --> 00:33:34.440
I was this pathetic waste of space.

600
00:33:36.200 --> 00:33:40.600
What if I actually am so discredited
they lose their case?

601
00:33:46.560 --> 00:33:49.400
[anchor] Twin brothers are due
in Glasgow High Court today.

602
00:33:49.480 --> 00:33:52.920
accused of killing a cyclist
and covering up their crime.

603
00:33:53.720 --> 00:33:57.320
Alexander and Robert McKellar
face life imprisonment

604
00:33:57.400 --> 00:34:01.080
if found guilty
of murdering Anthony Parsons.

605
00:34:02.560 --> 00:34:04.840
[Mike Wade] You have in the dock

606
00:34:04.920 --> 00:34:07.560
a man accused of killing somebody

607
00:34:07.640 --> 00:34:11.240
and the person
who's gonna testify against him.

608
00:34:11.760 --> 00:34:13.640
the woman he was going to marry.

609
00:34:14.720 --> 00:34:18.840
Whether you. uh. view court
as a spectacle or not.

610
00:34:19.440 --> 00:34:21.360
you know. that is high drama.

611
00:34:23.200 --> 00:34:26.640
If the Parsons family
were to see justice done.

612
00:34:26.720 --> 00:34:30.440
Caroline's testimony
was going to be absolutely crucial.

613
00:34:31.560 --> 00:34:35.760
[Brian] I thought that being
a woman of significant intelligence.

614
00:34:35.840 --> 00:34:38.800
she would be
a difficult witness to cross-examine.

615
00:34:38.880 --> 00:34:42.880
I anticipated that
she would be quite volatile.

616
00:34:43.480 --> 00:34:47.160
Nothing suggested she was going to be
an easy witness to deal with.

617
00:34:49.800 --> 00:34:51.880
[Caroline] I woke up early hours.

618
00:34:52.400 --> 00:34:54.360
My mum's laid out an outfit.

619
00:34:54.880 --> 00:34:58.840
I'm looking at it and I'm thinking.
"That doesn't even fit me anymore."

620
00:34:58.920 --> 00:35:00.920
[dark music plays]

621
00:35:01.760 --> 00:35:05.840
[Mike] It's an extraordinary feeling.
really. being in the court of justice.

622
00:35:06.440 --> 00:35:08.800
As people begin to gather.

623
00:35:08.880 --> 00:35:10.360
from the lawyers

624
00:35:10.440 --> 00:35:12.720
to this poor man's family.

625
00:35:13.720 --> 00:35:16.320
there's a rising sense of expectation.

626
00:35:19.360 --> 00:35:22.440
And then the accused
are brought up into the dock.

627
00:35:23.320 --> 00:35:26.200
These country lads
are wearing their best suits.

628
00:35:27.480 --> 00:35:29.520
They've had nice new haircuts.

629
00:35:30.080 --> 00:35:33.440
It's a moment of real tension.

630
00:35:37.080 --> 00:35:38.440
[Caroline] I was so ashamed…

631
00:35:38.960 --> 00:35:42.480
[sniffs] …of who I was
and what I'd become.

632
00:35:42.560 --> 00:35:43.640
[woman] Court.

633
00:35:44.520 --> 00:35:46.400
[Mike] And you're waiting for Caroline…

634
00:35:49.320 --> 00:35:50.800
to take the stand.

635
00:35:50.880 --> 00:35:52.600
[woman] Call the diet.
His Majesty's Advocate

636
00:35:52.680 --> 00:35:55.920
against Alexander McKellar
and Robert McKellar.

637
00:35:57.840 --> 00:36:01.360
And I just thought
I was going to let everyone down.

638
00:36:02.800 --> 00:36:04.080
And I just panicked.

639
00:36:04.160 --> 00:36:06.160
[urgent music plays]

640
00:36:10.720 --> 00:36:13.400
I wanted to get
as far away from there as possible.

641
00:36:19.800 --> 00:36:24.000
There was a sense that something
had gone wrong for the Crown.

642
00:36:24.080 --> 00:36:26.360
-[judge] Advocate Depute.
-Thank you. My Lord.

643
00:36:26.440 --> 00:36:27.440
I regret that I move

644
00:36:27.520 --> 00:36:30.120
that the case be adjourned
until tomorrow morning.

645
00:36:30.640 --> 00:36:31.960
Very well.

646
00:36:32.040 --> 00:36:34.280
[urgent music continues]

647
00:36:34.360 --> 00:36:37.320
[Mike] The no-show on the first day
of the star witness…

648
00:36:39.880 --> 00:36:42.040
it… it's just extraordinary.

649
00:36:42.120 --> 00:36:44.120
[urgent music fades out]

650
00:36:48.960 --> 00:36:50.160
[phone rings]

651
00:36:50.240 --> 00:36:52.600
[Margaret] The phone went.
It was the police.

652
00:36:52.680 --> 00:36:56.080
"She hasn't turned up. Where is she?"
And I'm saying. "She's not here."

653
00:36:56.800 --> 00:36:58.720
And now I don't know where she is.

654
00:36:59.840 --> 00:37:01.960
You're having to stop
your mind catastrophizing

655
00:37:02.040 --> 00:37:05.560
about what might have happened
or where she might have gone.

656
00:37:05.640 --> 00:37:07.640
[dramatic music plays]

657
00:37:09.480 --> 00:37:13.480
I just had this crazy notion
that if I found that bike.

658
00:37:13.560 --> 00:37:15.040
maybe it'd all be okay.

659
00:37:15.120 --> 00:37:18.440
I know where the bike is.
That's something else. It's not just me.

660
00:37:18.520 --> 00:37:22.920
[cries] You know?
It's not just the word of a crazy person.

661
00:37:23.680 --> 00:37:27.360
There might be proof they haven't found
that they did do this.

662
00:37:27.440 --> 00:37:29.080
[dramatic music continues]

663
00:37:30.000 --> 00:37:32.920
And so there wasn't much sense in it.
Of course there wasn't.

664
00:37:34.120 --> 00:37:36.800
So. basically. no signal.

665
00:37:37.600 --> 00:37:39.160
So no one knows I'm here.

666
00:37:39.840 --> 00:37:41.560
To get to that waterfall…

667
00:37:42.080 --> 00:37:42.920
Slight issue.

668
00:37:43.840 --> 00:37:45.160
…that's a long walk.

669
00:37:45.240 --> 00:37:47.200
If I go all the way round
with the flooding.

670
00:37:47.280 --> 00:37:49.040
that'll take another 40 minutes.

671
00:37:49.800 --> 00:37:50.720
But…

672
00:37:50.800 --> 00:37:51.680
Let's go.

673
00:37:51.760 --> 00:37:54.040
…I had half a bottle of wine
once I got out of the car.

674
00:37:54.120 --> 00:37:56.280
The adrenaline was
coursing through me so much.

675
00:37:56.360 --> 00:37:58.240
Fuck. [grunting]

676
00:37:58.320 --> 00:37:59.880
Shit. man! [yelps]

677
00:38:00.800 --> 00:38:03.120
I'm getting to that waterfall.
getting that bike.

678
00:38:03.200 --> 00:38:04.640
No one's gonna stop me.

679
00:38:04.720 --> 00:38:07.680
I'm gonna show the police.
I'm gonna do their job for them.

680
00:38:08.280 --> 00:38:10.280
Three miles in to an 18-mile hike.

681
00:38:10.800 --> 00:38:12.320
I haven't got much time.

682
00:38:13.080 --> 00:38:15.560
I was taking snaps of myself.

683
00:38:15.640 --> 00:38:17.160
Didn't send them to anyone.

684
00:38:18.160 --> 00:38:22.320
And I think there was this. "Look at me
and look at what I'm about to do…"

685
00:38:22.400 --> 00:38:26.320
And. "I'm this victim.
Like. look what people have done to me."

686
00:38:26.400 --> 00:38:27.360
What now?

687
00:38:28.360 --> 00:38:30.760
When you start something.
you've gotta finish it.

688
00:38:30.840 --> 00:38:32.240
You're…

689
00:38:33.000 --> 00:38:34.320
I'm not sane.

690
00:38:36.840 --> 00:38:40.560
You know. this was my home.
I lived here. I love it.

691
00:38:40.640 --> 00:38:42.360
I lost everything.

692
00:38:44.040 --> 00:38:45.680
I miss it so much.

693
00:38:48.320 --> 00:38:50.680
[disturbing music plays]

694
00:38:50.760 --> 00:38:54.200
[Mike] It would be fair to say
on that first morning when this happened.

695
00:38:54.280 --> 00:38:59.880
the defense team was a bit more upbeat
than the. uh. prosecution team. [laughs]

696
00:39:00.640 --> 00:39:03.720
If your key witness
is not prepared to take the stand.

697
00:39:03.800 --> 00:39:04.920
that's a problem.

698
00:39:05.880 --> 00:39:09.520
Dr. Muirhead did not appear
in answer to her citation.

699
00:39:10.680 --> 00:39:12.600
A warrant was sought for her arrest.

700
00:39:12.680 --> 00:39:14.440
[disturbing music continues]

701
00:39:14.520 --> 00:39:17.120
She had been sighted on the estate.

702
00:39:19.160 --> 00:39:20.480
[Caroline] Hello!

703
00:39:21.440 --> 00:39:23.200
I've only done seven miles.

704
00:39:23.880 --> 00:39:26.080
I was supposed to testify.
what. three hours ago?

705
00:39:27.040 --> 00:39:28.160
The hours are going by.

706
00:39:28.760 --> 00:39:29.920
They'll be looking for me.

707
00:39:31.600 --> 00:39:33.600
All the cars
are going to come along there.

708
00:39:34.200 --> 00:39:37.480
I've still got another. what.
seven miles to get to the dam?

709
00:39:37.560 --> 00:39:40.000
Then I heard
the low hum of the helicopter.

710
00:39:40.080 --> 00:39:41.160
I mean. it's echoing.

711
00:39:41.240 --> 00:39:42.200
[helicopter descends]

712
00:39:42.280 --> 00:39:43.800
They're coming. boys!

713
00:39:43.880 --> 00:39:45.360
Run into the barn.

714
00:39:46.800 --> 00:39:48.280
Seeing that helicopter

715
00:39:49.280 --> 00:39:52.640
took even. like. whatever little bit
of rational thought there was there.

716
00:39:52.720 --> 00:39:54.200
and then it was gone.

717
00:39:54.280 --> 00:39:57.080
I'm so fucking lucky
I got here before they did.

718
00:39:57.600 --> 00:39:59.800
I'm under a table. I'm in a shed.

719
00:39:59.880 --> 00:40:01.080
There's nobody here.

720
00:40:01.600 --> 00:40:03.720
There's no trace of me. right?

721
00:40:05.920 --> 00:40:09.360
For me to get to this waterfall.
I am running out of time.

722
00:40:11.560 --> 00:40:13.960
I needed a faster form of transport.

723
00:40:15.600 --> 00:40:18.000
[breathing heavily] Oh my God.
See if the keys are in this.

724
00:40:18.080 --> 00:40:19.160
Oh my God.

725
00:40:20.120 --> 00:40:23.000
Fucking idiots left the keys!

726
00:40:23.720 --> 00:40:25.920
Now. I have no idea
how to drive a tractor.

727
00:40:26.000 --> 00:40:27.640
[imitates tractor engine]

728
00:40:27.720 --> 00:40:28.920
Shit!

729
00:40:29.000 --> 00:40:30.720
Turn around. and there's the manual.

730
00:40:30.800 --> 00:40:33.240
still in its plastic casing.
in the back seat.

731
00:40:33.320 --> 00:40:34.640
And I went. "Right."

732
00:40:34.720 --> 00:40:36.600
With the manual on my lap.

733
00:40:36.680 --> 00:40:40.560
putting the key in. being like.
"Turn this. do that." then… Vroom!

734
00:40:41.840 --> 00:40:44.280
I have stolen

735
00:40:45.280 --> 00:40:46.560
a tractor.

736
00:40:49.040 --> 00:40:53.080
Oh… my… fucking…

737
00:40:55.320 --> 00:40:56.640
God!

738
00:40:56.720 --> 00:40:58.520
Whoo!

739
00:41:00.760 --> 00:41:03.160
I drove the tractor
to where the waterfall nearly is.

740
00:41:03.240 --> 00:41:04.880
Blocked the road.

741
00:41:05.840 --> 00:41:07.840
Now the police can't get past me.

742
00:41:09.480 --> 00:41:10.320
Fuck.

743
00:41:11.960 --> 00:41:12.840
Like…

744
00:41:14.040 --> 00:41:17.160
I mean. this is crazy!

745
00:41:19.160 --> 00:41:21.960
We see right there.
there's a wee cave bit behind.

746
00:41:22.480 --> 00:41:25.280
And the pressure of the water.
when you throw the bike down.

747
00:41:25.360 --> 00:41:27.000
it churns it up into the back.

748
00:41:27.080 --> 00:41:30.320
And… if that bike is still there.

749
00:41:31.360 --> 00:41:33.160
I'm going to try and find it.

750
00:41:33.680 --> 00:41:35.320
I'm wading through the water.

751
00:41:35.400 --> 00:41:38.800
I mean. the water is freezing cold.

752
00:41:41.800 --> 00:41:44.520
And the shock of the cold water

753
00:41:45.360 --> 00:41:48.120
actually made me very emotional.

754
00:41:51.920 --> 00:41:54.520
["Non. Je ne Regrette Rien" plays]

755
00:42:07.960 --> 00:42:09.960
[mouths]

756
00:42:14.080 --> 00:42:18.040
In that moment.
my brain was working so fast.

757
00:42:18.120 --> 00:42:21.880
Not logically. but so incredibly fast.

758
00:42:21.960 --> 00:42:24.360
I thought.
"Do you know what? Fuck it all."

759
00:42:24.440 --> 00:42:25.680
[sings along]

760
00:42:25.760 --> 00:42:27.800
"Non. je ne regrette rien."

761
00:42:35.400 --> 00:42:37.400
[sad string music plays]

762
00:42:41.920 --> 00:42:43.000
Mania.

763
00:42:43.680 --> 00:42:44.880
Psychosis.

764
00:42:48.120 --> 00:42:49.840
And that's what I'd become.

765
00:42:51.440 --> 00:42:54.800
You're an hysterical. broken person.

766
00:42:59.160 --> 00:43:02.120
Don't let anyone else

767
00:43:02.200 --> 00:43:04.800
get abandoned and broken like me.

768
00:43:06.240 --> 00:43:10.000
I have just fucked my whole life up.

769
00:43:10.640 --> 00:43:12.240
For what?

770
00:43:12.320 --> 00:43:15.320
For a man who actually killed somebody.

771
00:43:15.840 --> 00:43:19.520
And that grief.
and that loss. and that stress

772
00:43:19.600 --> 00:43:21.920
culminated into that

773
00:43:23.320 --> 00:43:25.480
psychotic finale.

774
00:43:25.560 --> 00:43:28.360
["Non. Je ne Regrette Rien" continues]

775
00:43:28.440 --> 00:43:31.520
I need to know if the bike is here.

776
00:43:32.040 --> 00:43:35.080
If there is something more than me.

777
00:43:35.160 --> 00:43:40.160
I did not start a murder trial
for something I didn't fucking see.

778
00:43:42.720 --> 00:43:44.720
["Non. Je ne Regrette Rien" continues]

779
00:43:53.560 --> 00:43:54.960
I am found at the waterfall.

780
00:43:55.040 --> 00:43:56.920
and I am then arrested

781
00:43:57.760 --> 00:43:59.440
for contempt of court.

782
00:44:01.000 --> 00:44:02.120
I never found the bike.

783
00:44:02.200 --> 00:44:04.520
["Non. Je ne Regrette Rien" continues]

784
00:44:06.400 --> 00:44:08.760
I then get taken to the High Court.

785
00:44:12.680 --> 00:44:14.600
["Non. Je ne Regrette Rien" ends]

786
00:44:20.440 --> 00:44:23.200
[pensive music plays]

787
00:44:23.280 --> 00:44:26.680
[Caroline breathes uneasily]

788
00:44:30.400 --> 00:44:32.120
I'm sitting there. waiting to testify.

789
00:44:34.040 --> 00:44:35.080
And I'm thinking.

790
00:44:35.760 --> 00:44:40.920
"My mum and dad
will be so angry and upset with me."

791
00:44:42.640 --> 00:44:45.240
The police called…

792
00:44:45.320 --> 00:44:46.160
Oh. yes.

793
00:44:46.240 --> 00:44:48.600
…and said they found her.

794
00:44:48.680 --> 00:44:50.560
[approaching footsteps]

795
00:44:50.640 --> 00:44:52.320
She faces prison.

796
00:44:53.320 --> 00:44:54.760
[pensive music continues]

797
00:44:54.840 --> 00:44:55.920
I was just

798
00:44:57.080 --> 00:44:59.160
stunned by the whole situation.

799
00:44:59.240 --> 00:45:00.840
I couldn't cope with it.

800
00:45:02.000 --> 00:45:06.080
So much of her young life has been wasted

801
00:45:06.160 --> 00:45:09.600
by this sequence of events.

802
00:45:09.680 --> 00:45:11.040
That pains me.

803
00:45:11.120 --> 00:45:12.520
Because. you know…

804
00:45:14.080 --> 00:45:16.800
young life is to be lived.

805
00:45:17.840 --> 00:45:20.240
And that… [cries]

806
00:45:20.320 --> 00:45:21.760
…hurts me.

807
00:45:25.440 --> 00:45:27.440
[pensive music fades out]

808
00:45:32.880 --> 00:45:36.160
[Mike] The next day the court reconvenes.

809
00:45:36.240 --> 00:45:39.680
I've heard various rumors
why Caroline hadn't shown.

810
00:45:40.240 --> 00:45:42.320
Someone told me
she'd been in the cells overnight.

811
00:45:42.400 --> 00:45:44.400
[urgent music plays]

812
00:45:45.680 --> 00:45:46.960
[Caroline] Court!

813
00:45:47.640 --> 00:45:49.200
[Mike] Sat in the court.

814
00:45:49.280 --> 00:45:52.120
We thought we were getting
a live court case.

815
00:45:52.200 --> 00:45:54.840
And it… it… it worked
in a completely different way.

816
00:45:54.920 --> 00:45:56.160
It was very unusual.

817
00:45:56.240 --> 00:46:00.120
I can advise that there has been
a development in the case.

818
00:46:01.080 --> 00:46:03.880
[Caroline] I was waiting
for the guard to take me to testify.

819
00:46:10.440 --> 00:46:12.440
[urgent music continues]

820
00:46:13.840 --> 00:46:15.280
[Mike] And in front of the court.

821
00:46:15.360 --> 00:46:19.560
the prosecutor requests
that the indictment is amended.

822
00:46:20.080 --> 00:46:23.520
My Lord. in relation to charge number one.

823
00:46:23.600 --> 00:46:27.640
in line 11. to delete the word "murder"

824
00:46:27.720 --> 00:46:30.000
and substitute the word "kill."

825
00:46:32.200 --> 00:46:34.560
[Mike] It's very significant indeed.

826
00:46:34.640 --> 00:46:38.040
The murder charge
has become unsustainable.

827
00:46:38.680 --> 00:46:43.960
I have instructions to tender
a plea of guilty to charge one.

828
00:46:44.040 --> 00:46:46.880
I received a telephone call
from the prosecution.

829
00:46:46.960 --> 00:46:50.480
If Mr. McKellar was prepared
to plead guilty to culpable homicide.

830
00:46:50.560 --> 00:46:52.640
the Crown would accept.

831
00:46:53.240 --> 00:46:57.160
Culpable homicide
is a crime less than murder.

832
00:46:57.240 --> 00:47:00.640
Those pleas are acceptable to the Crown.

833
00:47:00.720 --> 00:47:05.360
Because a plea was agreed.
then there is no trial.

834
00:47:08.080 --> 00:47:11.880
The twins Alexander and Robert McKellar
had been due to stand trial

835
00:47:11.960 --> 00:47:14.080
for the murder of Anthony Parsons.

836
00:47:14.160 --> 00:47:15.840
But today. here at the High Court.

837
00:47:15.920 --> 00:47:19.240
at the start of what was
expected to be a lengthy trial.

838
00:47:19.320 --> 00:47:24.280
Alexander instead pled guilty
to the lesser charge of culpable homicide

839
00:47:24.360 --> 00:47:27.800
whilst his brother Robert admitted
to teaming up with Alexander

840
00:47:27.880 --> 00:47:30.440
to hide and then bury the body.

841
00:47:30.520 --> 00:47:32.520
[dramatic music plays]

842
00:47:33.480 --> 00:47:37.240
[Caroline] The court official said to me
that "The boys have accepted a plea."

843
00:47:37.880 --> 00:47:39.560
"So you are free to leave."

844
00:47:41.400 --> 00:47:44.400
"And you don't have a criminal record
for contempt of court."

845
00:47:49.880 --> 00:47:52.600
"And the Parsons family
want to thank you very much."

846
00:48:00.800 --> 00:48:03.440
-[man] Did you go to the sentencing?
-[Caroline] I did.

847
00:48:04.160 --> 00:48:07.600
It was the final door to close.

848
00:48:07.680 --> 00:48:09.640
[woman] Call the diet.
Adjourned diet for sentence.

849
00:48:09.720 --> 00:48:10.800
His Majesty's Advocate

850
00:48:10.880 --> 00:48:13.160
against Alexander McKellar
and Robert McKellar.

851
00:48:13.240 --> 00:48:14.120
Please be seated.

852
00:48:15.480 --> 00:48:18.360
[Caroline] From where I was sitting.
I could see Sandy.

853
00:48:21.320 --> 00:48:22.160
And that…

854
00:48:23.440 --> 00:48:24.840
was really overwhelming.

855
00:48:25.600 --> 00:48:27.200
[Brian] Mr. McConnachie.

856
00:48:27.880 --> 00:48:30.240
[Caroline]
Sandy's barrister read a statement

857
00:48:30.320 --> 00:48:32.200
on Sandy's behalf to the judge.

858
00:48:33.480 --> 00:48:36.960
[Brian] He accepts that whilst
catastrophically injured.

859
00:48:37.040 --> 00:48:40.200
Mr. Parsons was alive at the time.

860
00:48:41.000 --> 00:48:42.280
The only explanation

861
00:48:43.480 --> 00:48:49.160
which he offers is simply fear and panic.

862
00:48:49.240 --> 00:48:54.400
Using his words. he says he was
too much of a coward to come clean.

863
00:48:54.920 --> 00:48:58.040
When he met Caroline.

864
00:48:58.120 --> 00:49:00.160
and she went to the police.

865
00:49:00.240 --> 00:49:04.040
he fully accepts that. ultimately.

866
00:49:04.120 --> 00:49:07.160
she made the right decision in doing so.

867
00:49:09.120 --> 00:49:12.320
Very well. Alexander McKellar
and Robert McKellar. please stand.

868
00:49:13.200 --> 00:49:16.200
[Caroline] Then the judge gave out
the boys' sentences.

869
00:49:17.680 --> 00:49:19.240
[judge] Robert McKellar.

870
00:49:19.320 --> 00:49:21.520
the sentence which I now impose on you

871
00:49:21.600 --> 00:49:25.640
is one of a period of imprisonment
of five years and three months.

872
00:49:25.720 --> 00:49:27.600
Alexander McKellar.

873
00:49:27.680 --> 00:49:32.080
you have pleaded guilty
to grave and serious crimes.

874
00:49:32.160 --> 00:49:34.520
He wasn't convicted of murder.

875
00:49:35.400 --> 00:49:38.120
but he did take an innocent man's life.

876
00:49:39.680 --> 00:49:42.240
So for me.
he's a coward and he's a killer.

877
00:49:43.120 --> 00:49:44.160
[judge] Alexander McKellar.

878
00:49:44.760 --> 00:49:50.000
I will impose on you a single sentence
of imprisonment of 12 years.

879
00:49:51.480 --> 00:49:52.920
That is all.

880
00:49:53.800 --> 00:49:55.800
[dramatic music plays]

881
00:49:58.880 --> 00:50:01.600
[Mike] At sentencing.
a friend of Tony Parsons said these boys

882
00:50:01.680 --> 00:50:03.240
had got away with murder.

883
00:50:05.120 --> 00:50:08.960
There was a sense
that without Caroline's evidence.

884
00:50:09.040 --> 00:50:11.400
the full facts of this case.

885
00:50:11.480 --> 00:50:15.000
the full horror of it. perhaps.
never quite got across.

886
00:50:18.240 --> 00:50:23.720
I can well imagine that the family feel
there hasn't been a closure. in a way.

887
00:50:25.600 --> 00:50:27.480
If people think or wonder.

888
00:50:27.560 --> 00:50:30.480
if I had testified.
would they have had a harsher sentence?

889
00:50:32.040 --> 00:50:33.360
The state I was in.

890
00:50:34.320 --> 00:50:35.240
who knows?

891
00:50:38.120 --> 00:50:41.840
[David] Had Caroline Muirhead
decided to say nothing.

892
00:50:42.520 --> 00:50:46.040
then Mr. Parsons
would still be buried on the estate.

893
00:50:46.640 --> 00:50:49.520
She did absolutely the right thing.

894
00:50:50.160 --> 00:50:54.120
[Mike] You have to applaud her bravery.

895
00:50:54.800 --> 00:50:57.480
but the pressure
must have been unbearable.

896
00:50:57.560 --> 00:51:00.400
You'd be a hard person indeed
not to sympathize with her.

897
00:51:00.480 --> 00:51:03.200
[man] Does part of you sympathize
with Caroline Muirhead?

898
00:51:03.280 --> 00:51:04.120
No.

899
00:51:04.200 --> 00:51:06.240
The whole circumstances

900
00:51:06.320 --> 00:51:10.080
in which she did not deal with things

901
00:51:10.160 --> 00:51:13.120
in a manner
which people would expect her to.

902
00:51:13.200 --> 00:51:15.000
take away. I think.

903
00:51:15.080 --> 00:51:19.040
from any sympathetic view
I might feel about her.

904
00:51:21.120 --> 00:51:25.720
If the criminal justice agencies

905
00:51:25.800 --> 00:51:29.560
want people to come forward as witnesses.

906
00:51:29.640 --> 00:51:33.040
they have to do better
at every single stage.

907
00:51:34.400 --> 00:51:37.680
There needs to be a real awareness

908
00:51:37.760 --> 00:51:42.600
of the trauma experienced by witnesses.

909
00:51:47.280 --> 00:51:50.080
[dramatic music fades out]

910
00:51:52.000 --> 00:51:54.760
[Caroline] I have no regrets
about coming forward.

911
00:51:55.280 --> 00:51:58.280
This is what happened to me.
It's my story.

912
00:51:59.680 --> 00:52:01.720
I just hope other people
can learn from it.

913
00:52:01.800 --> 00:52:03.600
so they don't make
the same mistakes I made.

914
00:52:03.680 --> 00:52:07.320
Because. my God.
I made a hell of mistakes.

915
00:52:10.200 --> 00:52:12.200
["Change" plays]

916
00:52:14.920 --> 00:52:18.560
I am so lucky
to be able to move forward in my life.

917
00:52:20.160 --> 00:52:21.960
I've moved to the coast.

918
00:52:22.040 --> 00:52:24.280
I've managed to get myself clean.

919
00:52:26.400 --> 00:52:28.320
I now see a psychiatrist.

920
00:52:30.240 --> 00:52:33.200
And I tackle
a lot of the insecurities that led me

921
00:52:33.280 --> 00:52:36.040
to be in the vulnerable relationship
to begin with.

922
00:52:38.400 --> 00:52:41.520
♪ Change… ♪

923
00:52:41.600 --> 00:52:43.120
[woman] Three. two. one. smile!

924
00:52:44.560 --> 00:52:47.840
[Caroline] I've got
a much better relationship with my family.

925
00:52:48.760 --> 00:52:49.880
♪ Like skin… ♪

926
00:52:49.960 --> 00:52:51.080
I met someone new.

927
00:52:52.120 --> 00:52:55.080
who is incredibly kind.

928
00:52:55.840 --> 00:52:57.160
When you love yourself.

929
00:52:58.320 --> 00:53:00.360
you will attract healthy love.

930
00:53:00.440 --> 00:53:01.520
♪ Like the leaves… ♪

931
00:53:01.600 --> 00:53:03.480
Onwards and upwards.

932
00:53:03.560 --> 00:53:04.640
♪ Like a butterfly… ♪

933
00:53:04.720 --> 00:53:07.400
-[man] That's it.
-[gasps] Thank God.

934
00:53:08.040 --> 00:53:09.240
♪ Would you live forever… ♪

935
00:53:09.320 --> 00:53:11.160
-We're done.
-[man] We're done. Caroline.

936
00:53:14.960 --> 00:53:20.680
♪ While everything around passes? ♪

937
00:53:22.640 --> 00:53:28.040
♪ Would you smile forever
Never cry? ♪

938
00:53:29.480 --> 00:53:35.040
♪ While everything you know passes ♪

939
00:53:37.160 --> 00:53:43.240
♪ Death's like a door ♪

940
00:53:43.320 --> 00:53:50.120
♪ To a place we've never been before ♪

941
00:53:51.400 --> 00:53:56.760
♪ Death's like space ♪

942
00:53:58.200 --> 00:54:00.520
♪ The deep sea ♪

943
00:54:01.800 --> 00:54:04.240
♪ The suitcase ♪

944
00:54:05.920 --> 00:54:11.160
♪ Would you stare forever at the sun ♪

945
00:54:12.920 --> 00:54:17.560
♪ Never watch the moon rising? ♪

946
00:54:19.960 --> 00:54:25.320
♪ Would you walk forever in the light ♪

947
00:54:26.960 --> 00:54:33.280
♪ To never learn the secret
Of the quiet night? ♪

948
00:54:38.640 --> 00:54:40.640
["Change" fades out]
